quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  71,11,He causes the sky to send torrents down upon you
  71,12,"and He supplies you with wealth and children, and grants you gardens and even grants you rivers"
  71,13,´What is wrong that you do not expect God to have any dignity
  71,14,while He has created you over and over again
  71,15,Have you not (all) considered how God created seven matching Heavens
  71,16,"He has set the moon as a light among them, and set the sun up as a source of light"
  71,17,God makes you grow out of the earth like plants
  71,18,"Later He will return you to it, and bring you forth once more"
  71,19,´God has laid the earth out as a carpet for you
  71,20,so you may travel around on highways which lead through mountain passes.´
  71,21,"Noah said: \"My Lord, they have defied me and followed after someone whose money and children will only increase [their chance of] losing"
  71,22,They have hatched a great plot
  71,23,"and said: ´Do not forsake your gods: do not leave Wadd, nor Suwa, nor Yaghuth, nor Yauq, nor Nasr!´"
  71,24,They have led so many astray; just let wrongdoers go even farther astray!´
  71,25,"Because of their mistakes, they were drowned and dispatched into the Fire. They did not find they had any supporters apart from God"
  71,26,"Noah said: \"My Lord, do not leave any disbelievers with homes upon the earth"
  71,27,"If You should leave them any, they will lead Your servants astray and will only breed loose-living disbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents, as well as anyone who enters my house as a believer, plus believing men and believing women! Do not increase wrongdoers in anything except destruction"